# SVG Graphics & Animation Assignment üöÄ

This repository contains a specialized exploration of **Scalable Vector Graphics (SVG)**. The project demonstrates how to create complex visual elements, custom branding, and interactive animations using pure HTML and XML-based drawing instructions.

## üìù Project Overview

This project showcases the versatility of SVGs by moving beyond simple images into the world of coordinate-based math and declarative animations. It serves as a technical demonstration of how to build high-quality, resolution-independent graphics that remain crisp at any zoom level.

### Key Features:
* **Vector Geometry:** Implementation of custom Polygons (Pentagons and Stars) and complex Paths.
* **Typography in SVG:** Stylized text rendering with custom stroke and fill properties.
* **SMIL Animations:** Native SVG animations including scaling, rotation, opacity pulsing, and path-stroke drawing.
* **Zero Dependencies:** Built entirely with standard HTML5; no external CSS or JavaScript libraries required.

---

## üõ†Ô∏è Technologies Used

| Technology | Purpose |
| :--- | :--- |
| **HTML5** | Document structure and containerization. |
| **SVG 2.0** | Vector graphics rendering and coordinate mapping. |
| **SMIL** | Native declarative animations for SVG elements. |

