## üöÄ How to Run the Project

You can run this project on your local machine in seconds without any complex setup.

1.  **Clone the Repository:**
    ```bash
    git clone [https://github.com/sarthaksm29-blip/HTML-CSS-assignments.git](https://github.com/sarthaksm29-blip/HTML-CSS-assignments.git)
    ```
2.  **Navigate to the Directory:**
    ```bash
    cd HTML-CSS-assignments
    ```
3.  **Open the File:**
    * Simply **double-click** the `index.html` file to view it in your default web browser.
    * Alternatively, if using **VS Code**, right-click the file and select `Open with Live Server`.

---

## üìà Future Improvements

To further enhance this project, the following features could be added:
* **Responsiveness:** Use the `viewBox` attribute to ensure graphics scale perfectly across mobile and desktop devices.
* **CSS Keyframes:** Transition the animations from SMIL to CSS `@keyframes` for better performance and support in modern browsers like Safari.
* **Interactivity:** Add JavaScript `EventListener` functions to trigger animations based on user clicks or mouse hovers.
* **Accessibility (A11y):** Integrate `<title>` and `<desc>` tags within each SVG for better screen-reader support.

